Hand-sketched engineering-notebook infographic on a cream background (#F7F4EA).
Confident charcoal ink linework (#2D2D2D), architectural drawing quality, subtle
paper grain. Accent colours: deep teal (#1A6B6B) and burnt orange (#C85A2A) only.
Wide 16:9 composition, generous margins, one clear focal idea, no clutter, no
photorealism, no gradients, no watermark. All text hand-lettered in a clean
draughtsman's capitals style. CRITICAL TEXT RULE: the ONLY text in the entire image is the strings listed below, each appearing EXACTLY ONCE, spelled exactly as written. Every other surface — stamps, seals, books, cards, signs, meters, coins, papers, stones, screens — is completely blank or carries only abstract decorative marks that are clearly NOT letters or numbers. Do not invent captions, tags, titles, stamps, or labels of any kind.

A ledger page sketch. Left column: a single teal agent figure with one short straight task-line beneath it — nothing written beside it, no checkbox, no tag. Right column: five orbs in a committee circle, their deliberation drawn as an expensive tangle of burnt-orange thread. Above the tangle a running cost meter drawn as a blank dial face with only a needle — no words, numbers, or coloured danger arc on the dial; the needle and dial rim are burnt orange (#C85A2A), never red. A magnifying glass hovers over the tangle. Do NOT write CHEAP or repeat any caption text on the artwork.
TEXT (exactly, each once): headline "COORDINATION HAS A PRICE"; left caption "one competent agent — low overhead"; right caption "free-text committees — token burn, error spirals"; bottom line "measure the transaction cost, then design for it".
